# üß≠ Pathfinding Visualizer

An interactive Pathfinding Visualizer built using **HTML, CSS, and JavaScript** to demonstrate how different graph traversal and shortest-path algorithms work on a grid.

This project visually compares algorithms based on:
- nodes visited
- shortest path length
- execution time

---

## üöÄ Features

- üìå Set **Start** and **Target** nodes
- üß± Draw and erase **walls**
- üßπ Clear path / walls / entire board
- ‚ö° Control **animation speed**
- üß† Visual comparison of algorithms
- üìä Performance metrics displayed:
  - Time taken (ms)
  - Visited cells
  - Path length

---

## üß† Algorithms Implemented

- **DFS (Depth First Search)**
- **BFS (Breadth First Search)**
- **Dijkstra‚Äôs Algorithm**
- **A\* Search Algorithm**
- **Greedy Best First Search**

---

## üìä Performance Metrics

Each algorithm execution displays:
- **Time Taken** ‚Äì computation time using `performance.now()`
- **Visited Cells** ‚Äì number of nodes explored
- **Path Length** ‚Äì length of the final path (if found)

> ‚ö†Ô∏è Note: Time measured is algorithm execution time, not animation time.

